cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a machine learning approach for detecting abnormal lung sounds using features extracted from audio files. This falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a large health survey dataset and the potential application in healthcare suggest the sub-categories of healthcare (cs.HC) and systems and control (cs.SY). The evaluation of classifiers and feature extraction methods also suggests the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
